The paper deals with the downlink performance of a precoding scheme in a massive MIMO cellular network, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), and multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the impact of pilot contamination, which is a common issue in wireless communication systems and falls under the category of communication (cs.COM).
